250
00:12:52,662 --> 00:12:53,796
And he couldn't
take a night off?

251
00:12:53,864 --> 00:12:55,731
And who knows
who he had watching her?

252
00:12:55,799 --> 00:12:57,967
Some secretary, another whore?

253
00:12:58,034 --> 00:13:00,035
But...

254
00:13:00,103 --> 00:13:04,306
That's him, not Sally.

255
00:13:04,374 --> 00:13:07,710
<i>Little girls do do this,</i>

256
00:13:07,777 --> 00:13:10,312
And not just ones
from broken homes.

257
00:13:13,083 --> 00:13:14,683
I know.

258
00:13:17,487 --> 00:13:19,155
I was impulsive.

259
00:13:19,222 --> 00:13:22,458
I'll apologize.

260
00:13:22,526 --> 00:13:24,527
Having had a girl this age,

261
00:13:24,594 --> 00:13:26,762
I can tell you that punishment
will only make this worse.

262
00:13:28,798 --> 00:13:30,799
So when you're
up there apologizing,

263
00:13:30,867 --> 00:13:33,235
You let her know
that she's going to go
to the hairdresser

264
00:13:33,303 --> 00:13:35,437
And she can go
on her sleepover.

265
00:13:36,740 --> 00:13:38,974
Reward her?

266
00:13:39,042 --> 00:13:41,043
- Really?
- Really.

267
00:13:49,686 --> 00:13:51,353
You're soft, you know that?

268
00:14:03,300 --> 00:14:05,434
There you are.
The Honda meeting's today.

269
00:14:05,502 --> 00:14:06,969
And before
you bite my head off,

270
00:14:07,037 --> 00:14:09,205
I'm up to date on the protocol
with the help of Cooper.

271
00:14:09,272 --> 00:14:12,308
We don't have to do anything
but avoid criticizing them
or giving advice.

272
00:14:12,375 --> 00:14:14,443
I ran into Ted Chaough.

273
00:14:14,511 --> 00:14:16,745
How are they in this thing
and how could you
not know that?

274
00:14:16,813 --> 00:14:18,480
This guy's drafting off of us.

275
00:14:18,548 --> 00:14:21,517
For the record,
it's j.W.T., c.G.C. And us.

276
00:14:21,551 --> 00:14:24,753
Now if you don't mind,
I have to get some gifts wrapped

277
00:14:24,821 --> 00:14:26,755
And get these chrysanthemums
out of the building.

278
00:14:26,823 --> 00:14:28,457
Apparently
they symbolize death.

279
00:14:28,525 --> 00:14:30,693
So much conflicting
information.

280
00:14:36,333 --> 00:14:37,433
Allow me to show you around.

281
00:14:40,770 --> 00:14:42,705
Our offices are probably more
modern than you've seen,

282
00:14:42,772 --> 00:14:44,974
But that's the kind
of company we are...
forward-thinking.

283
00:14:48,912 --> 00:14:51,413
This is what we call
the creative lounge.

284
00:14:51,481 --> 00:14:53,515
We can't tell you
how it happens,

285
00:14:53,583 --> 00:14:55,150
<i>But it does
happen here.</i>

286
00:14:55,218 --> 00:14:56,952
This is too difficult.

287
00:14:57,020 --> 00:14:59,521
Well, tell them something.

288
00:15:02,259 --> 00:15:04,693
This is Joan Harris,
our chief hostess.

289
00:15:04,761 --> 00:15:06,295
I'd like you to meet
Ichiro Kamura

290
00:15:06,363 --> 00:15:08,297
And Hachi Saito.

291
00:15:08,365 --> 00:15:11,500
Nice to meet you.
I hope no one's taken
you to Benihana.

292
00:15:11,568 --> 00:15:13,802
David Ogilvy.

293
00:15:13,870 --> 00:15:16,639
I've got a very good list
of steakhouses.
Just ask.

294
00:15:24,114 --> 00:15:25,814
Not very subtle, aren't they?

295
00:15:25,882 --> 00:15:27,850
No, they are not.

296
00:15:30,420 --> 00:15:33,589
We are most happily
looking forward

297
00:15:33,657 --> 00:15:35,591
To presentation.

298
00:15:35,659 --> 00:15:37,326
Not now, I hope.

299
00:15:38,495 --> 00:15:42,998
We want more driver
for motorcycle.

300
00:15:43,066 --> 00:15:45,601
And we shall endeavor
to make that happen.

301
00:15:45,669 --> 00:15:48,437
And now that we are finished,

302
00:15:48,505 --> 00:15:51,307
Please accept our modest gifts.

303
00:15:52,709 --> 00:15:54,843
I cannot accept.

304
00:15:54,911 --> 00:15:56,712
A small token.

305
00:15:59,082 --> 00:16:01,717
No thank you.

306
00:16:01,785 --> 00:16:03,719
Please.
You are our guests.

307
00:16:03,787 --> 00:16:05,421
Thank you.

308
00:16:07,857 --> 00:16:11,493
- Open it.
- No. Later, of course.

309
00:16:13,296 --> 00:16:14,963
It's a cantaloupe.

310
00:16:17,901 --> 00:16:19,601
Johnny Walker red.

311
00:16:25,542 --> 00:16:27,309
<i>- Thank you very much.
- Thank you.</i>

312
00:16:30,513 --> 00:16:34,149
I'm sorry.
I didn't know
this meeting was happening.

313
00:16:34,217 --> 00:16:36,852
Then again,
I know how some people
love surprises.

314
00:16:36,920 --> 00:16:39,221
I apologize, gentlemen,

315
00:16:39,289 --> 00:16:42,091
But for some reason
I was not informed.

316
00:16:42,158 --> 00:16:44,393
In fact, someone set
a long lunch for me
with Randolph.

317
00:16:44,461 --> 00:16:48,831
Well, it was last minute
and now, unfortunately,
drawn to a close.

318
00:16:48,898 --> 00:16:52,134
I have to warn you
they won't know it's over
until you drop the big one...

319
00:16:52,202 --> 00:16:53,836
Twice.

320
00:16:53,903 --> 00:16:55,404
The meeting is not over.

321
00:16:55,472 --> 00:16:58,173
We have yet
to present the rules.

322
00:16:58,241 --> 00:17:00,075
So now you're dictating terms.

323
00:17:05,849 --> 00:17:08,951
Mr. Kamura, Mr. Saito,
this is Roger sterling.

324
00:17:10,253 --> 00:17:12,988
This is their translator
Akira Takahashi.

325
00:17:14,657 --> 00:17:19,795
We give each firm $3,000

326
00:17:19,863 --> 00:17:23,699
For a competitive presentation.

327
00:17:23,767 --> 00:17:27,503
In this packet
are the conditions
for the competition.

328
00:17:27,570 --> 00:17:30,038
We don't want any conditions.
We want it to be unconditional.

329
00:17:32,208 --> 00:17:33,275
Akira, go ahead,
tell 'em what I said.

330
00:17:33,343 --> 00:17:35,444
Roger, stop it.

331
00:17:35,512 --> 00:17:37,813
- These men are our guests.
- I know exactly who
these men are.

332
00:17:37,881 --> 00:17:39,782
You think you can just
come in here and we'll
Fawn all over you?

333
00:17:39,849 --> 00:17:42,751
We beat you
and we'll beat you again.

334
00:17:42,819 --> 00:17:44,386
We don't want
any of your jap crap.

335
00:17:44,454 --> 00:17:48,023
<i>So sayonara.</i>

336
00:17:54,697 --> 00:17:58,100
If you could only know
my embarrassment.

337
00:18:00,603 --> 00:18:03,572
His wife's very sick.
He's been drinking a lot.

338
00:18:10,046 --> 00:18:11,814
You have our rules.

339
00:18:11,881 --> 00:18:14,016
We very much look forward
to your prestation.

340
00:18:27,664 --> 00:18:29,631
You don't get
to kill this account.

341
00:18:29,699 --> 00:18:32,034
- Well, you know how they are.
Maybe it'll kill itself.
- Enough.

342
00:18:32,101 --> 00:18:33,902
I'm not even talking
about money right now.

343
00:18:33,970 --> 00:18:36,405
I'm talking about
the kind of work you
could do for those people.

344
00:18:36,473 --> 00:18:38,040
Have you seen
that motorcycle?
They love design.

345
00:18:38,107 --> 00:18:39,775
As long as my name's
in that lobby,

346
00:18:39,843 --> 00:18:42,010
I get to choose whom
I do business with.

347
00:18:42,078 --> 00:18:44,446
I've got a lot better reasons
than you had with Jantzen.

348
00:18:44,514 --> 00:18:46,281
Jantzen was over.

349
00:18:46,349 --> 00:18:48,217
I made a pledge
to a lot of men
you'll never meet

350
00:18:48,284 --> 00:18:50,185
Not to do business with them.

351
00:18:50,253 --> 00:18:52,788
Christ on a cracker,
where do you get off?

352
00:18:52,856 --> 00:18:55,257
You know what?
You weren't there.
You weren't anywhere.

353
00:18:55,325 --> 00:18:56,692
I'm sorry you can't understand.

354
00:18:56,759 --> 00:18:58,360
It's been almost 20 years.

355
00:18:58,428 --> 00:19:00,796
Whether you like it or not,
the world has moved on.

356
00:19:00,864 --> 00:19:02,698
These are not the same people.

357
00:19:02,765 --> 00:19:04,566
How could that be?
I'm the same people!

358
00:19:04,634 --> 00:19:06,568
You don't think
I know what you're doing?

359
00:19:06,636 --> 00:19:08,804
You're wrapping yourself
in the flag

360
00:19:08,872 --> 00:19:10,806
So you can keep me
from bringing in an account

361
00:19:10,874 --> 00:19:12,741
Because you know
every chip I make,

362
00:19:12,809 --> 00:19:15,010
We become less dependent
on lucky strike

363
00:19:15,078 --> 00:19:17,045
And therefore
less dependent on you.

364
00:19:17,113 --> 00:19:19,181
- Why you little...
- Roger!

365
00:19:22,852 --> 00:19:24,353
Get him out of here.

366
00:19:24,420 --> 00:19:26,588
The rest of us are trying
to build something.

367
00:19:32,862 --> 00:19:34,563
He's right.

368
00:19:49,300 --> 00:19:51,234
Where would you hide a coin?

369
00:19:51,302 --> 00:19:53,437
You'd spend it, wouldn't you?

370
00:19:53,504 --> 00:19:55,973
Well, I do know where it is.
I'll tell you.

371
00:19:56,040 --> 00:19:57,541
<i>Then tell me.</i>

372
00:19:57,608 --> 00:19:58,842
<i>I'll make
a bargain with you.</i>

373
00:19:58,910 --> 00:20:01,912
Let these two go.
Keep me. I'll tell you.

374
00:20:04,649 --> 00:20:06,850
<i>- Promise.
- No.</i>

375
00:20:06,918 --> 00:20:08,685
<i>Then no deal.</i>

376
00:20:30,942 --> 00:20:33,310
- What are you doing?
- Nothing.

377
00:20:33,378 --> 00:20:34,511
Laura.

378
00:20:36,547 --> 00:20:37,781
Go upstairs.

379
00:20:48,526 --> 00:20:50,894
Hold still.
I'll get it.

380
00:20:54,365 --> 00:20:57,067
What's the problem?
Is she sick?

381
00:20:57,135 --> 00:20:58,969
I would've come and gotten her.

382
00:20:59,037 --> 00:21:01,738
No.
The slumber party
ended early.

383
00:21:04,075 --> 00:21:05,308
I'd like to speak to Betty.

384
00:21:07,145 --> 00:21:09,079
Okay.
Honey?

385
00:21:12,583 --> 00:21:14,818
Is everything all right?

386
00:21:14,886 --> 00:21:16,853
No, it's not.

387
00:21:16,921 --> 00:21:19,456
Could you leave us
alone for a moment?

388
00:21:25,196 --> 00:21:27,931
I found Sally behaving
inappropriately.

389
00:21:27,999 --> 00:21:30,200
What'd she do?

390
00:21:31,869 --> 00:21:33,837
She was in our den on the couch

391
00:21:33,905 --> 00:21:35,639
Playing with herself.

392
00:21:36,908 --> 00:21:38,575
What?

393
00:21:38,643 --> 00:21:41,311
I don't know what goes on here,

394
00:21:41,379 --> 00:21:43,313
But that kind of behavior
is not allowed in my house

395
00:21:43,381 --> 00:21:45,449
And certainly not
in the presence
of my daughter.

396
00:21:48,453 --> 00:21:51,254
I am...

397
00:21:52,957 --> 00:21:54,925
Very sorry for this behavior

398
00:21:54,992 --> 00:21:56,993
And so is Sally.

399
00:21:59,597 --> 00:22:01,465
I would've done the same thing.

400
00:22:04,502 --> 00:22:06,136
Well...

401
00:22:06,204 --> 00:22:08,138
I'm sorry about that.

402
00:22:10,675 --> 00:22:12,742
I should go.

403
00:22:23,688 --> 00:22:25,455
What is wrong with you?

404
00:22:27,925 --> 00:22:29,960
You don't do those things.

405
00:22:30,027 --> 00:22:32,696
<i>You don't do them in private
and you especially don't
do them in public.</i>

406
00:22:35,967 --> 00:22:37,934
- You have nothing to say?
- I didn't do anything.

407
00:22:38,002 --> 00:22:40,337
Don't you dare lie to me.
I'll cut your fingers off.

408
00:22:40,404 --> 00:22:43,306
Go to bed.
We'll deal with
this in the morning.

409
00:22:48,379 --> 00:22:49,980
What happened?

410
00:22:54,418 --> 00:22:56,453
I'm mortified.

411
00:22:56,521 --> 00:22:59,489
I'm so embarrassed.

412
00:22:59,557 --> 00:23:01,992
what happened?

413
00:23:03,961 --> 00:23:05,762
She caught Sally...

414
00:23:07,899 --> 00:23:09,533
Playing with herself.

415
00:23:16,040 --> 00:23:18,041
What's wrong with her?

416
00:23:18,109 --> 00:23:20,043
That woman will tell everybody.

417
00:23:20,111 --> 00:23:24,347
why is she doing this?

418
00:23:24,415 --> 00:23:26,983
I told you if it got serious,

419
00:23:27,051 --> 00:23:29,085
Ere is a solution.

420
00:23:29,153 --> 00:23:31,888
I don't want to do that, Henry.

421
00:23:31,956 --> 00:23:34,024
It's one thing after another.

422
00:23:34,091 --> 00:23:36,059
What's wrong with her?

423
00:23:36,127 --> 00:23:39,763
Maybe it's time
we let a professional
answer that question.

424
00:23:39,830 --> 00:23:41,865
Henry...

425
00:23:44,101 --> 00:23:45,735
I went to a psychiatrist once.

426
00:23:48,005 --> 00:23:50,040
What?
Why?

427
00:23:50,107 --> 00:23:52,776
Because I was unhappy.

428
00:23:52,843 --> 00:23:54,578
And I don't think
it helps anything.

429
00:23:58,015 --> 00:24:00,150
I hate to think how much worse

430
00:24:00,218 --> 00:24:01,918
It would have been
for Eleanor without one.

431
00:24:01,986 --> 00:24:04,354
They train them just for kids.

432
00:24:04,422 --> 00:24:06,356
We got ours from the school.

433
00:24:06,424 --> 00:24:09,459
I'm saying this
not because I'm so sure

434
00:24:09,527 --> 00:24:11,261
There's something
wrong with her,

435
00:24:11,329 --> 00:24:13,296
But I think this is
very hard on you two.

436
00:24:17,368 --> 00:24:19,536
- When did you go?
- Years ago.

437
00:24:19,604 --> 00:24:21,471
I was bored.

438
00:24:23,574 --> 00:24:25,942
- Can we leave it at that?
- Of course.

439
00:24:51,202 --> 00:24:53,403
Miss Blankenship,
any luck on that call
to California?

440
00:24:53,471 --> 00:24:55,572
<i>I'm sorry.
No answer.</i>

441
00:24:55,640 --> 00:24:58,541
<i>Misters Peters and Pryce
to see you.</i>

442
00:24:58,609 --> 00:25:00,510
Send them in.

443
00:25:00,578 --> 00:25:04,848
I think we're okay,
but everything they do
is inside out.

444
00:25:04,915 --> 00:25:07,884
I got a call this morning
from my contact Masao

445
00:25:07,952 --> 00:25:10,720
Telling me that the meeting
was a Margaret Dumont-sized
disaster,

446
00:25:10,788 --> 00:25:13,356
But then... lane?

447
00:25:13,424 --> 00:25:15,558
Then nearly
20 minutes later
Masao called me

448
00:25:15,626 --> 00:25:18,228
And set a time
for our presentation.

449
00:25:18,296 --> 00:25:20,363
Look, there's probably
a guy like Roger
at every firm.

450
00:25:20,431 --> 00:25:22,632
They've outgrown it
and we haven't.

451
00:25:22,700 --> 00:25:25,969
Roger has something to say.

452
00:25:26,037 --> 00:25:30,273
<i>Mr. Cooper
and Mr. Sterling.</i>

453
00:25:31,609 --> 00:25:33,276
I realize that I
should not at this point

454
00:25:33,344 --> 00:25:35,845
Limit our potential clients
in any way.

455
00:25:35,913 --> 00:25:38,715
Next account,
no matter what it is,
you'll have my full support.

456
00:25:38,783 --> 00:25:40,116
And?

457
00:25:42,453 --> 00:25:44,554
Look, I know it's an old one

458
00:25:44,622 --> 00:25:47,190
And I have to let it go
just for my health alone,

459
00:25:47,258 --> 00:25:50,527
And, uh...
well, hell, it's over.

460
00:25:50,594 --> 00:25:53,596
Your contrition wouldn't
have gotten you out of this,
but you're lucky.

461
00:25:53,664 --> 00:25:56,099
They called and gave us
an appointment anyway.

462
00:25:56,167 --> 00:25:58,034
That means nothing.

463
00:25:58,102 --> 00:26:01,538
<i>- It's over.
- No, Bert, I said
we have a meeting.</i>

464
00:26:01,605 --> 00:26:06,276
It's most likely that
they are expecting us
to come in and resign.

465
00:26:06,344 --> 00:26:08,645
How do you get there from here?

466
00:26:10,715 --> 00:26:12,615
Have we received a gift?

467
00:26:14,452 --> 00:26:15,885
We should have
gotten one yesterday.

468
00:26:15,953 --> 00:26:17,887
I haven't.

469
00:26:17,955 --> 00:26:20,623
Miss Blankenship,
have I received any
packages today?

470
00:26:20,691 --> 00:26:22,025
<i>Yes.</i>

471
00:26:23,561 --> 00:26:24,861
Could you bring it in, please?

472
00:26:30,601 --> 00:26:33,603
It says "don" on it.

473
00:26:33,671 --> 00:26:35,338
Give it to him.

474
00:26:42,413 --> 00:26:45,782
"help me, Honda,
help help me, Honda.
Love, Teddy Chaouh."

475
00:26:48,252 --> 00:26:51,388
<i>- So there is no gift.
- That's how they work.</i>

476
00:26:51,455 --> 00:26:54,858
They want us to go in there,
bow down and beg them
to chop our heads off

477
00:26:54,925 --> 00:26:57,861
Because we disgraced ourselves.
How could you admire
these animals?

478
00:26:57,928 --> 00:26:59,529
Would you shut up?
They're businessmen

479
00:26:59,597 --> 00:27:01,030
And you insulted them
to their face.

480
00:27:01,098 --> 00:27:02,465
I'm expecting a child.

481
00:27:04,435 --> 00:27:07,203
Jai alai, clearasil, now Honda.

482
00:27:07,271 --> 00:27:09,339
Chaough wins another one
by default.

483
00:27:09,407 --> 00:27:12,442
- He's not going to win.
- I'm not wasting
that appointment.

484
00:27:12,510 --> 00:27:14,144
We need to do something

485
00:27:14,211 --> 00:27:15,979
That will make them
notice us... fireworks.

486
00:27:16,046 --> 00:27:17,981
- Do you have a campaign?
- No.

487
00:27:18,048 --> 00:27:20,950
But I will
and we're gonna shoot
a whole commercial for it...

488
00:27:21,018 --> 00:27:23,119
Something outrageous,
something graphic.

489
00:27:23,187 --> 00:27:25,388
The rules limit us
to boards and copy.

490
00:27:25,456 --> 00:27:27,824
It specifically says
no finished work.

491
00:27:27,892 --> 00:27:30,126
Because no one's ever won
an account by breaking
the rules?

492
00:27:30,194 --> 00:27:33,296
- Not with the Japanese.
- You're trying to tell me

493
00:27:33,364 --> 00:27:35,665
If we put our backs into this,
we couldn't turn their heads?

494
00:27:35,733 --> 00:27:38,301
$3,000 is all we have.

495
00:27:38,369 --> 00:27:41,237
That should buy
about four seconds
of your commercial.

496
00:27:41,305 --> 00:27:43,072
You don't think it's worth
going out of pocket?

497
00:27:43,140 --> 00:27:44,474
What pocket?

498
00:27:44,542 --> 00:27:47,143
A spec commercial
will eat up our ability

499
